Guiding Light.I DESK: The final terminal will be highlighted with a glowing blue outline, leading you straight to your last objective.
Guiding Light.II DESK: The final two terminal will be highlighted with a glowing blue outline, leading you straight to your last objective.
Guiding Light.III DESK: Each time a terminal is hacked, all other available terminals will be highlighted temporarily.

Adrenaline Boost.I DESK: Saving a teammate ignites a surge of energy. Gain a 3 seconds speed boost after a successful rescue.
Adrenaline Boost.II DESK: Saving a teammate ignites a surge of energy. Gain a 5 seconds speed boost after a successful rescue.
Adrenaline Boost.III DESK: Saving a teammate ignites a surge of energy. Gain a 7 seconds speed boost after a successful rescue.

Lone Survivor.I DESK: When the odds are against you, your determination heightens. Decoding speed increases by 20% with each eliminated survivor.
Lone Survivor.II DESK: When the odds are against you, your determination heightens. Decoding speed increases by 50% with each eliminated survivor.
Lone Survivor.III DESK: When the odds are against you, your determination heightens. Decoding speed increases by 80% with each eliminated survivor.

Healing Hands.I DESK: Your swift hands mend wounds faster, allowing you to heal temmates 10% quicker.
Healing Hands.II DESK: Your swift hands mend wounds faster, allowing you to heal temmates 25% quicker.
Healing Hands.III DESK: Your swift hands mend wounds faster, allowing you to heal temmates 40% quicker.

Locked Eyes.I DESK: Temporarily highlights the locations of all other survivors for 3 seconds after completing a terminal.
Locked Eyes.II DESK: Temporarily highlights the locations of all other survivors for 5 seconds after completing a terminal.
Locked Eyes.III DESK: Temporarily highlights the locations of all other survivors for 7 seconds after completing a terminal.

Pitfall.I DESK: Allows you to sabotage a ball pit, making it inaccessible for 20 seconds.
Pitfall.II DESK: Allows you to sabotage a ball pit, making it inaccessible for 40 seconds.
Pitfall.III DESK: Allows you to sabotage a ball pit, making it inaccessible for 60 seconds.

Clocking Out.I DESK: After completing a terminal, gain a speed boost for 5 seconds.
Clocking Out.II DESK: After completing a terminal, give yourself and any nearby survivors a speed boost for 3 seconds.
Clocking Out.III DESK: After the escapes are opened, give yourself a minor speed boost for the rest of the match. This effect will only trigger while full health.

Dusting Off.I DESK: When completing a healing action on another survivor, reduce their capture progress by 5%. (Doesn't work with self care)
Dusting Off.II DESK: When completing a healing action on another survivor, reduce their capture progress by 10%, It'll also reduce your capture progress by 5%. (Doesn't work with self care)
Dusting Off.III DESK: When completing a healing action on another survivor, reduce their capture progress by 15%, It'll also reduce your capture progress by 8%. (Doesn't work with self care)

Hidden Charge.I DESK: Even in failure, you remain unnoticed. Failing to hack a terminal will not alert the animatronic. (1 use)
Hidden Charge.II DESK: Even in failure, you remain unnoticed. Failing to hack a terminal will not alert the animatronic. (2 uses)
Hidden Charge.III DESK: Even in failure, you remain unnoticed. Failing to hack a terminal will not alert the animatronic. (3 uses)

Third Eye.I DESK: As the exit opens, your instincts sharpen, revealing the animatronic's location for 5 seconds.
Third Eye.II DESK: As the exit opens, your instincts sharpen, revealing the animatronic's location for 10 seconds.
Third Eye.III DESK: As the exit opens, your instincts sharpen, revealing the animatronic's location for 15 seconds.

Self Care.I DESK: Grants you an item that let you heal for 30 seconds with a 240 seconds cooldown.
Self Care.II DESK: Grants you an item that let you heal for 30 seconds with a 180 seconds cooldown.
Self Care.III DESK: Grants you an item that let you heal for 30 seconds with a 120 seconds cooldown.

Shielded Escape.I DESK: Rescuing a teammate from a ball pit grants you a temporary force field, protecting you and teammate from the next hit. Lasts 1 seconds.
Shielded Escape.II DESK: Rescuing a teammate from a ball pit grants you a temporary force field, protecting you and teammate from the next hit. Lasts 1.5 seconds.
Shielded Escape.III DESK: Rescuing a teammate from a ball pit grants you a temporary force field, protecting you and teammate from the next hit. Lasts 2 seconds.

Tank Build.I DESK: While hacking a terminal you only take 35 damage if attacked.
Tank Build.II DESK: 35% chance to reduce damage taken when attacked to 35.
Tank Build.III DESK: Increase max health by 50, but your walkspeed is reduced by 10%.

Trimmers.I DESK: While nearby a survivor being carried, boost their escape progress by 10%. If they manage to escape you will be slowed down 20% for 3 seconds.
Trimmers.II DESK: While nearby a survivor being carried, boost their escape progress by 20%. If they manage to escape you will be slowed down 20% for 3 seconds.
Trimmers.III DESK: While nearby a survivor being carried, boost their escape progress by 30%. If they manage to escape you will be slowed down 20% for 3 seconds.

Sprint.I DESK: Gain a speed boost for 5 seconds with a 40 seconds cooldown.
Sprint.II DESK: Gain a speed boost for 5 seconds with a 35 seconds cooldown.
Sprint.III DESK: Gain a speed boost for 5 seconds with a 30 seconds cooldown.

Rekindle.I DESK: If you are the last survivor you gain a permanent 10% speed boost.
Rekindle.II DESK: If you are the last survivor you open doors 15% faster and hack terminals 5% faster.
Rekindle.III DESK: If you are the last survivor you gain a 10% speed boost, open doors 15% faster and hack terminals 5% faster.

Guardian Angel.I DESK: After you capture percentage reaches 95% you'll be rescued. 1 time use.
Guardian Angel.II DESK: After you capture percentage reaches 90% you'll be rescued. 1 time use.
Guardian Angel.III DESK: After you capture percentage reaches 85% you'll be rescued. 1 time use.

Resolve.I DESK: After being rescued, gain a 5% speed boost for 3 seconds.
Resolve.II DESK: After being rescued, gain a 7% speed boost for 4 seconds.
Resolve.III DESK: After being rescued, gain a 10% speed boost for 5 seconds.

Dim Presence.name: Dim Presence
Dim Presence.desk: Darkness works in favor of the animatronic. Reduces the range of the glow by 10%/20%/30%, making it easier to creep up on unsuspecting survivors.

Predators Trail.name: Predators Trail
Predators Trail.desk: Fresh wounds leave a path to follow. After striking a survivor, their footprints become visible for 1/2/3 seconds, making it easier to track them down.

Rescue Signal.name: Rescue Signal
Rescue Signal.desk: A rescue won't go unheard. The animatronic is alerted when a survivor has been rescued for a ball pit, temporarily highlighting its location for 1/2/3 seconds.

Brute Force.name: Brute Force
Brute Force.desk: Nothing stands in the way. Opens doors 10%/20%/30% faster, reducing obstacles between the animatronic and its prey.

Listening Mode.name: Listening Mode
Listening Mode.desk: Silence sharpens the senses. While standing still, activates ability to detect survivors hacking nearby. A distinct sound or notification alerts both the animatronic and survivors if detected. Lasts 1/2/3 seconds.

Final Stand.name: Final Stand
Final Stand.desk: The hunt isn't over yet. When the exit doors are unlocked, the animatronic's speed increases by 7.5%/15%/20%, making last-minute escapes even more dangerous.

Marked One.name: Marked One
Marked One.desk: Strikes leave a lasting mark. When a survivor is hit, nearby teammates will be revealed with a red outline for a short duration.

Sugar Crash.name: Sugar Crash
Sugar Crash.desk: Can throw a cupcake at the nearby survivor to deal damage and weaken their escape.

Amplified Fear.name: Amplified Fear
Amplified Fear.desk: Strums a chilling chord, sending shockwaves that slow down nearby survivors in the animatronic's presence.

Circuit Breaker.name: Circuit Breaker
Circuit Breaker.desk: The hooked metal hand can temporarily sabotage terminals by striking them, stalling survivors and slowing their progress.

Springlocked.name: Springlocked
Springlocked.desk: Instantly knocks survivors with a powerful attack. Passive cooldown 45 seconds.

Mangled.name: Mangled
Mangled.desk: Can grab the nearest survivor within 50 studs (Dodgeable). 30 seconds cooldown.

Silent Steps.name: Silent Steps
Silent Steps.desk: Silences footsteps and camera shake influence for 5/9/13 seconds, making attacks more surprising. 30 seconds cooldown.

Short Circuit.name: Short Circuit
Short Circuit.desk: Resets the progress of the nearest terminal. 90 seconds cooldown.

Vengeance.name: Vengeance
Vengeance.desk: When a survivor is downed, anyone within 35 studs of the downed survivor is instantly struck with residual damage.

Scorchpath.name: Scorchpath
Scorchpath.desk: Can create a blazing wall of fire anywhere, forming a temporary barrier of heat that punishes anyone who dares to cross it.

Companion Bear.name: Companion Bear
Companion Bear.desk: A little companion plushie that can be placed anywhere, once placed, it grants the ability to teleport back to the plushie.

Ice Cream Lure.name: Ice Cream Lure
Ice Cream Lure.desk: Drops an ice cream cone that detects nearby survivors. Can be removed by survivors.

Deadly Grace.name: Deadly Grace
Deadly Grace.desk: Twirls around during sprints, dealing low damage (20) around itself with each spin, but the spring has a 300% longer cooldown.

Limb Reaper.name: Limb Reaper
Limb Reaper.desk: Hitting a survivor will cause them to lose a limb that will either reduce movement speed or hacking speed. Survivors can retrieve their limbs.

Bon Bon Bite.name: Bon Bon Bite
Bon Bon Bite.desk: Attacking a survivor will poison every nearby survivors for 10 damage every seconds for 5 seconds. 30 seconds cooldown.

Remote Anchor.name: Remote Anchor
Remote Anchor.desk: Animatronic can drop a trap that trips survivors.

Please Stand By.name: Please Stand By
Please Stand By.desk: Some terminals are trapped. Hacking a trapped terminal grants the animatronic a speed boost and cooldown reduction.

Digital Reality.name: Digital Reality
Digital Reality.desk: Transfers into the digital reality by becoming invisible for a while. When turning visible, cannot move and attack for a split second. 35 seconds cooldown.

Silent Angel.name: Silent Angel
Silent Angel.desk: The angels burn animatronic's eyes, it can't look at them for long... But they can't move while it does. The animatronic can teleport to any angel.

Ignited One.name: Ignited One
Ignited One.desk: Strikes leave a lasting mark. When a survivor is hit, nearby teammates will be revealed with a red outline for a short duration.

Toxic Crash.name: Toxic Crash
Toxic Crash.desk: Can throw a cupcake a toxic cupcake that creates a toxic cloud.

Amplified Terror.name: Amplified Terror
Amplified Terror.desk: Strums a chilling chord, blinding and slowing nearby survivors.

Blackout Breaker.name: Blackout Breaker
Blackout Breaker.desk: The hooked metal hand can temporarily sabotage terminals by striking them and regresses progress by 15%. Can only be used 2 times on the same terminal.

The Joy Of Creation.name: The Joy Of Creation
The Joy Of Creation.desk: Animatronic emits a searing pulse, scorching survivors. If they are caught in the pulse, they leave burning marks.
